OL,3,CHomelessness charity could close after
OL,4,Cenergy bill spirals into thousands
OL,6,FJason tells ITV News' Sam Blackledge
OL,7,Fhis charity cannot afford a #4,000
OL,8,Fenergy bill
OL,10,FA Plymouth charity for the homeless
OL,11,Fsays it may have to close because it
OL,12,Fcan't afford to pay a #4,000 energy
OL,13,Fbill.
OL,15,FHope for the Homeless, based at the
OL,16,FGarage Cafe in Union Street, provides
OL,17,Ffood and clothing for vulnerable
OL,18,Fpeople in the city.JThe charity says
OL,19,Fit is disputing the electricity bill,
OL,20,Fand has been forced to in a bid to
OL,21,Fsurvive.
